83
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:40,291
It's everything they had
from the past ten years or so.

84
00:05:43,583 --> 00:05:45,000
Peppermint?!
What the hell!

85
00:05:45,083 --> 00:05:46,791
What's this...?
Is the little boy whining

86
00:05:46,875 --> 00:05:49,208
about being able
to use my library?

87
00:05:49,291 --> 00:05:51,208
The library belongs
to the students!

88
00:05:51,291 --> 00:05:53,958
No, the library belongs
to the StuCo president.

89
00:05:54,041 --> 00:05:56,083
Just what are
you looking for?

90
00:05:56,166 --> 00:05:57,875
Information about a fire

91
00:05:57,958 --> 00:06:00,166
that supposedly killed
a family named Hoshimura.

92
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:01,625
A fire?

93
00:06:01,708 --> 00:06:03,541
That's a tough one because
those don't always make it

94
00:06:03,625 --> 00:06:04,916
in the newspaper, right?

95
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:08,416
Well, I'm just
following a hunch.

96
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:11,291
♪ "If you want to die..."

97
00:06:11,375 --> 00:06:12,583
Kun-chan's hot!

98
00:06:12,666 --> 00:06:14,208
Loser alert.

99
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:15,583
OURI.

100
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:17,541
Still going to
tonight's show with me?

101
00:06:17,625 --> 00:06:18,916
Oh. About that...

102
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:20,583
I've got it all
planned out!

103
00:06:20,666 --> 00:06:21,875
She's going to make
eye contact with me

104
00:06:21,958 --> 00:06:23,250
and know she's in love!

105
00:06:23,333 --> 00:06:25,583
Now first, we find out
where her dressing room is.

106
00:06:25,666 --> 00:06:26,625
If she's not there...

107
00:06:26,708 --> 00:06:28,125
I'm not going, Ushi.

108
00:06:28,208 --> 00:06:29,833
Huh?

109
00:06:29,916 --> 00:06:31,083
Shoot.

110
00:06:31,166 --> 00:06:33,500
I so did not want
to go with my sister.

111
00:06:33,583 --> 00:06:37,000
"Shikabane, uh uh uh..."

112
00:06:38,041 --> 00:06:39,541
Hey, hey...

113
00:06:39,625 --> 00:06:40,583
What now?

114
00:06:40,666 --> 00:06:42,041
I know what this is about.

115
00:06:42,125 --> 00:06:44,458
This has to do with
some girl, doesn't it?

116
00:06:44,541 --> 00:06:45,833
No way. What?

117
00:06:45,916 --> 00:06:47,416
Ok, then.

118
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:50,041
Explain why you're so touchy
whenever I ask you about it.

119
00:06:50,125 --> 00:06:51,416
It's just, you know...

120
00:06:51,500 --> 00:06:52,833
that name, Hoshimura...

121
00:06:52,916 --> 00:06:55,000
I remember it...

122
00:07:04,666 --> 00:07:06,041
Hello...

123
00:07:06,125 --> 00:07:07,125
What?

124
00:07:07,208 --> 00:07:09,041
Hoshimura?

125
00:07:11,625 --> 00:07:13,666
I'll be right back.

126
00:07:16,375 --> 00:07:18,750
That's when it started.

127
00:07:18,833 --> 00:07:22,125
When Brother would come home
all bruised and beaten.

128
00:07:34,958 --> 00:07:37,666
You should get a life.

129
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:40,375
How much of that
did you hear?

130
00:07:40,458 --> 00:07:44,041
I notice those perverted
Anime posters are finally gone.

131
00:07:45,166 --> 00:07:47,041
Yeah, I took the girls
away to a safer,

132
00:07:47,125 --> 00:07:48,708
more loving place where
they can be appreciated

133
00:07:48,791 --> 00:07:49,875
in the way they deserve.

134
00:07:49,958 --> 00:07:51,166
Unlike this place,

135
00:07:51,250 --> 00:07:53,250
where they keep getting
thrown in the garbage.

136
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:55,416
You expect me to have a
serious talk with that trash

137
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:57,041
staring back at me?

138
00:07:57,125 --> 00:07:58,833
Can we talk?

139
00:08:00,458 --> 00:08:01,750
Kun Osaki.

140
00:08:01,833 --> 00:08:05,375
Princess of pop, her new
album's already number one.

141
00:08:05,458 --> 00:08:08,625
However...
Kun Osaki is dead.

142
00:08:09,958 --> 00:08:12,583
There were rumors
of her frailty.

143
00:08:12,666 --> 00:08:15,375
That she'd fainted in the
studio recording her album.

144
00:08:15,458 --> 00:08:18,250
Her publicist assured everyone
she was merely exhausted...

145
00:08:18,333 --> 00:08:20,541
... but it was more
serious than that.

146
00:08:20,625 --> 00:08:22,291
But, how could they have
covered up the death

147
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:23,458
of someone so famous?

148
00:08:23,541 --> 00:08:25,000
In the world
of show business,

149
00:08:25,083 --> 00:08:27,625
just about everybody's
connected to the underworld.

150
00:08:27,708 --> 00:08:28,916
She's no different.

151
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,416
But I suspect
her manager's the one

152
00:08:30,500 --> 00:08:32,583
with the necessary
connections.

153
00:08:32,666 --> 00:08:34,083
Then that must mean...

154
00:08:34,166 --> 00:08:37,041
He knows she's a Shikabane,
but he chooses to hide it.

155
00:08:37,125 --> 00:08:38,583
People have been
disappearing around her

156
00:08:38,666 --> 00:08:40,625
for quite some time now...

157
00:08:40,708 --> 00:08:43,833
a news station employee...
cab driver, landlord...

158
00:08:43,916 --> 00:08:46,333
too many to be
just coincidence.

159
00:08:46,416 --> 00:08:48,208
Come to think of it,
she hasn't been on TV

160
00:08:48,291 --> 00:08:51,791
or seen in public
at all for years.

161
00:08:51,875 --> 00:08:54,125
You're right,
it's all a big cover-up.

162
00:08:54,208 --> 00:08:55,583
Yes...

163
00:08:55,666 --> 00:08:57,500
But for whatever reason she's
suddenly having a concert

164
00:08:57,583 --> 00:08:59,041
right here in our town.

165
00:08:59,125 --> 00:09:01,708
You're going to that concert
to find the source of her energy

166
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:03,916
so you can dissolve it.

167
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,916
Be careful, Makina.

168
00:09:21,416 --> 00:09:22,833
Hello.
I have a delivery

169
00:09:22,916 --> 00:09:25,416
for someone in
Kun-Osaki san's office.

170
00:09:25,500 --> 00:09:27,583
Oh, yeah. Fifth floor
conference room -

171
00:09:27,666 --> 00:09:29,083
got a big entourage.

172
00:09:29,166 --> 00:09:31,958
Guess she thinks she
needs that many people.

173
00:09:32,041 --> 00:09:33,458
Thanks.

174
00:09:35,416 --> 00:09:37,500
Big entourage?

175
00:09:52,041 --> 00:09:54,541
Excuse me, ma'am did
somebody order a--

176
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:01,375
What'd she do?
From that distance!

177
00:10:02,666 --> 00:10:05,708
So you're the one who's
trying to kill our product.

178
00:10:07,250 --> 00:10:10,041
We've heard
so much about you.

179
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:15,625
Move back!

180
00:10:15,708 --> 00:10:17,458
Move back!

181
00:10:21,958 --> 00:10:23,666
How did you know
I was coming?

182
00:10:23,750 --> 00:10:25,375
Somebody...
called us!

183
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:28,291
It doesn't matter
who called.

184
00:10:28,375 --> 00:10:30,750
Would you like me to sing
for you, my biggest fan?

185
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:32,875
But you're dead, Osaki.

186
00:10:32,958 --> 00:10:35,916
Eh, obviously not.

187
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:37,583
As long as I sing, I live.

188
00:10:37,666 --> 00:10:38,833
Song's over.

189
00:10:38,916 --> 00:10:40,166
Dead girl.

190
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:46,583
Get her!

191
00:10:55,708 --> 00:10:57,333
Hold it right there buddy.

192
00:10:57,416 --> 00:10:59,833
We know you're working
with the woman upstairs.

193
00:10:59,916 --> 00:11:02,416
Who, little ol' meeee???

194
00:11:06,833 --> 00:11:08,125
I'm not a wussy!

195
00:11:08,208 --> 00:11:09,791
Hey!
You wussy boy!

196
00:11:09,875 --> 00:11:11,500
No, I'm not, I'm not!

197
00:11:11,583 --> 00:11:13,583
Wussy boy! Wussy boy!

198
00:11:13,666 --> 00:11:15,125
All right, kids;
that's enough!

199
00:11:15,208 --> 00:11:18,750
Stop annoying Ouri;
you know he doesn't like it.

200
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:20,708
We can't have any
fun around here!

201
00:11:20,791 --> 00:11:22,291
So, did you find anything?

202
00:11:22,375 --> 00:11:25,250
Well, as
I understand it...

203
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:28,541
Mr. Hoshimura had some
connection to our temple here.

204
00:11:28,625 --> 00:11:30,250
What?
The Kougon Sect?

205
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:32,791
When my father died,
Mr. Hoshimura visited me

206
00:11:32,875 --> 00:11:34,083
after the funeral.

207
00:11:34,166 --> 00:11:36,458
I think he may have
been Keisei's senior?

208
00:11:36,541 --> 00:11:37,875
I'm not sure.

209
00:11:37,958 --> 00:11:40,708
But I never heard that
his house had burned down.

210
00:11:40,791 --> 00:11:43,416
Is there an address,
or landmark I can go by?

211
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:45,541
Why don't you ask Keisei?

212
00:11:45,625 --> 00:11:49,125
Keisei...
can't know about this.

213
00:12:35,208 --> 00:12:36,958
The temple...

214
00:12:50,750 --> 00:12:52,333
Hey! What the hell!

215
00:12:52,416 --> 00:12:53,708
Get her!

216
00:12:58,041 --> 00:12:59,125
Keisei!

217
00:12:59,208 --> 00:13:00,541
There she is!

218
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:02,708
She's still alive?!

219
00:13:02,791 --> 00:13:04,416
Hold it!

220
00:13:07,583 --> 00:13:09,333
Hey! C'mon!
Get her!

221
00:13:22,083 --> 00:13:24,250
Be quiet back there!

222
00:13:24,333 --> 00:13:25,875
I'm sorry for
all the trouble.

223
00:13:25,958 --> 00:13:27,458
We need Sojo Takamine

224
00:13:27,541 --> 00:13:29,041
with the prefectural
police to get involved.

225
00:13:29,125 --> 00:13:30,416
They can take
it from here.

226
00:13:30,500 --> 00:13:31,708
The prefectural?

227
00:13:31,791 --> 00:13:33,166
That's right. They're
the only ones allowed

228
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:35,291
to know anything
about Shikabane.

229
00:13:35,375 --> 00:13:37,500
And they're also the ones
who most frequently deal

230
00:13:37,583 --> 00:13:38,500
with the yakuza.

231
00:13:38,583 --> 00:13:40,333
Understood.

232
00:13:42,375 --> 00:13:43,208
My apologies.

233
00:13:43,291 --> 00:13:44,541
It's ok.

234
00:13:44,625 --> 00:13:46,958
We're sworn to protect
and defend you, Sho-Sojo.

235
00:13:47,041 --> 00:13:48,875
I'm just doing my job.

236
00:13:48,958 --> 00:13:51,541
Yes, but it doesn't make
things any easier for you.

237
00:13:51,625 --> 00:13:54,000
I know how hard it must be
for you to have to attack

238
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,833
a living human being.

239
00:14:07,083 --> 00:14:08,083
Hey, hey, hey!

240
00:14:08,166 --> 00:14:10,250
There is some crazy
shit happening!

241
00:14:10,333 --> 00:14:11,708
Ushi?

242
00:14:11,791 --> 00:14:14,750
Ya hear? Kun-Chan's performance
has just been cancelled!

243
00:14:14,833 --> 00:14:16,541
Something about a fight
between yakuza groups?

244
00:14:16,625 --> 00:14:17,958
Nobody knows anything,

245
00:14:18,041 --> 00:14:20,708
but somebody's saying
that Kun-chan was shot!

246
00:14:20,791 --> 00:14:22,833
What? Someone
shot her?

247
00:14:22,916 --> 00:14:24,708
Now they're saying the
hit-man was a woman?!

248
00:14:24,791 --> 00:14:26,958
I just hope
Kun-chan's alright.

249
00:14:27,041 --> 00:14:29,000
Things are getting crazy
in front of the CD shop.

250
00:14:29,083 --> 00:14:30,583
I'll call you again later.

251
00:14:30,666 --> 00:14:32,041
[Disconnect tone]

252
00:14:52,125 --> 00:14:53,250
Makina...

253
00:14:53,333 --> 00:14:55,458
Hoshimura...

254
00:14:55,541 --> 00:14:57,500
So you can read.

255
00:14:58,541 --> 00:14:59,750
Yes.

256
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:01,750
Me and my
entire family.

257
00:15:01,833 --> 00:15:03,916
This is where
we're buried.

258
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,458
It's true?

259
00:15:05,541 --> 00:15:08,083
It was a massacre,
when we died.

260
00:15:08,166 --> 00:15:10,333
When they burned my
family in the temple.

261
00:15:10,416 --> 00:15:12,250
But as a Shikabane Hime...

262
00:15:12,333 --> 00:15:14,750
I'll have my
vengeance one day.

263
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:16,500
If you got that...

264
00:15:16,583 --> 00:15:18,250
then please respect it

