00:15:18,333 --> 00:15:20,708
and don't ever show
your face to me again.

266
00:15:20,791 --> 00:15:22,250
Why?

267
00:15:22,333 --> 00:15:23,416
Why?

268
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:26,875
Of course. I want
to know more about you.

269
00:15:26,958 --> 00:15:28,875
We are the dead.

270
00:15:28,958 --> 00:15:30,916
We are defiled.

271
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,708
It's immoral for humans
to get close to us.

272
00:15:33,791 --> 00:15:35,666
If you get
anymore involved--

273
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:37,958
[phone ringing]

274
00:15:38,041 --> 00:15:39,708
Hello?

275
00:15:39,791 --> 00:15:40,750
Are you okay?

276
00:15:40,833 --> 00:15:42,166
Where are you?

277
00:15:42,250 --> 00:15:43,166
I'm fine.

278
00:15:43,250 --> 00:15:45,208
I'm taking care
of everything.

279
00:15:45,291 --> 00:15:46,750
Were you hurt at all?

280
00:15:46,833 --> 00:15:49,458
Who's that,
who're ya talking to?

281
00:15:49,541 --> 00:15:50,916
Don't worry!

282
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:52,541
Okay?

283
00:15:56,875 --> 00:15:58,500
To tell you the truth,
I was running away.

284
00:15:58,583 --> 00:15:59,958
I had no plan.

285
00:16:00,041 --> 00:16:01,916
I didn't even know
where I was going.

286
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:05,000
Or how or why
I ended up here at all.

287
00:16:05,083 --> 00:16:07,791
I just found myself here.

288
00:16:07,875 --> 00:16:08,833
Makina...

289
00:16:08,916 --> 00:16:10,583
Tell your friend,
I'm sorry.

290
00:16:10,666 --> 00:16:11,583
Huh?

291
00:16:11,666 --> 00:16:13,166
About the concert.

292
00:16:13,250 --> 00:16:15,958
I was only trying
to protect them.

293
00:16:16,041 --> 00:16:18,916
You mean you're the
one who attacked Osaki?!

294
00:16:27,791 --> 00:16:29,333
You should be resting.

295
00:16:29,416 --> 00:16:31,416
I just tried
to murder a rock star.

296
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,000
I can't stay here.

297
00:16:33,083 --> 00:16:35,833
Both the police and the yakuza
will be after me for that.

298
00:16:35,916 --> 00:16:37,208
But.

299
00:16:37,291 --> 00:16:41,000
I'm not about to leave
you here all by yourself.

300
00:16:41,083 --> 00:16:42,541
It's just that Brother
sort of took me in

301
00:16:42,625 --> 00:16:43,833
when I was three.

302
00:16:43,916 --> 00:16:46,041
And had nowhere
else to go.

303
00:16:46,125 --> 00:16:48,458
He said that he
couldn't leave me alone.

304
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:50,208
We may not really
be related...

305
00:16:50,291 --> 00:16:52,083
but we're brothers.

306
00:17:25,750 --> 00:17:27,791
Come on Kun, we have to
get you to a safer place!

307
00:17:27,875 --> 00:17:29,500
I wanna sing.
I wanna sing!

308
00:17:29,583 --> 00:17:30,833
I wanna sing!

309
00:17:30,916 --> 00:17:32,250
Of course.

310
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:34,583
Even up until now, those
who you killed were even--

311
00:17:34,666 --> 00:17:36,041
I didn't kill them!

312
00:17:36,125 --> 00:17:38,583
Uh, yes, of course.
Certainly not Kun...

313
00:17:38,666 --> 00:17:42,041
Those people interfered
with my song.

314
00:17:42,125 --> 00:17:43,500
They interfered!

315
00:17:43,583 --> 00:17:45,458
They interfered!

316
00:17:45,541 --> 00:17:48,541
They interfered!

317
00:17:50,041 --> 00:17:51,000
Kun-chan!

318
00:17:51,083 --> 00:17:53,166
What a terrible song.

319
00:17:56,166 --> 00:17:58,375
But it'll sound great
when you sing it in Hell...

320
00:17:58,458 --> 00:18:01,541
it's just the living
who can't stand it.

321
00:18:01,625 --> 00:18:03,375
That's really harsh!

322
00:18:38,791 --> 00:18:41,458
You got smacked
by a dead girl!

323
00:18:41,541 --> 00:18:43,958
Why are you with her?!
After all she's done.

324
00:18:44,041 --> 00:18:45,958
She's the strongest
being I've ever seen.

325
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:48,916
Certainly more
so than you, little brat.

326
00:18:54,583 --> 00:18:57,333
Well, damn.

327
00:18:57,416 --> 00:18:58,708
What are you
still doing here?

328
00:18:58,791 --> 00:19:00,083
I'll be just fine.

329
00:19:00,166 --> 00:19:02,041
Like hell, you're fine!

330
00:19:02,125 --> 00:19:03,375
Look at you!

331
00:19:03,458 --> 00:19:05,250
...your wounds are getting
worse by the minute...

332
00:19:05,333 --> 00:19:07,666
When I saw you before,
they started healing right away,

333
00:19:07,750 --> 00:19:09,083
but now...

334
00:19:09,166 --> 00:19:10,541
Shut up.

335
00:19:10,625 --> 00:19:13,291
Each Shikabane Hime has
an emotional and physical bond

336
00:19:13,375 --> 00:19:15,416
to a specific human.

337
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:18,250
And anytime that
human is nearby...

338
00:19:18,333 --> 00:19:21,333
She receives his Rune,
or life energy.

339
00:19:21,416 --> 00:19:23,583
With her body regenerated,
she is once again

340
00:19:23,666 --> 00:19:27,291
able to utilize her abilities
to their fullest extent.

341
00:19:27,375 --> 00:19:29,958
That specific human being
is referred to as...

342
00:19:30,041 --> 00:19:31,791
a contracted monk.

343
00:19:31,875 --> 00:19:33,250
Uh, Brother!

344
00:19:36,875 --> 00:19:38,916
So you're "just
fine," are you?

345
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:42,541
I told you not
to come, remember?

346
00:19:42,625 --> 00:19:44,458
What else could
I have done?

347
00:19:44,541 --> 00:19:47,541
Of course I came,
I'm your contracted monk.

348
00:20:02,791 --> 00:20:05,125
Stay here,
I got this.

349
00:20:08,791 --> 00:20:12,291
Makina, hold her
back by using this.

350
00:20:12,375 --> 00:20:13,875
Brother!

351
00:20:26,791 --> 00:20:30,208
♪ If you just can't go on,

352
00:20:32,791 --> 00:20:34,291
You had a beautiful voice.

353
00:20:34,375 --> 00:20:36,750
That's why you always
wanted to sing, right?

354
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:39,916
♪ I will care for it,

355
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:43,041
But! Your voice
is no good anymore!

356
00:20:43,125 --> 00:20:45,416
It's smothered by
your own twisted obsession

357
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:48,250
with eternal life and the idea
that you can sing forever.

358
00:20:48,333 --> 00:20:50,208
You couldn't accept
your fate as a human,

359
00:20:50,291 --> 00:20:53,625
so you abandoned
humanity altogether.

360
00:20:53,708 --> 00:20:56,833
And now, no one wants
to hear your voice.

361
00:20:56,916 --> 00:20:58,875
I understand your pain!

362
00:20:58,958 --> 00:21:02,541
But your song is defiled now,
it speaks of nothing but death!

363
00:21:07,458 --> 00:21:09,333
Brother!

364
00:21:12,208 --> 00:21:15,708
This is Shikimi
grown in holy water.

365
00:21:15,791 --> 00:21:18,083
Looks like it's working.

366
00:21:20,458 --> 00:21:23,041
Makina...
you take over...

367
00:21:23,125 --> 00:21:25,333
the only ones who can
kill Shikabane are...

368
00:21:25,416 --> 00:21:27,375
those who were created
for that purpose...

369
00:21:27,458 --> 00:21:29,083
Shikabane Hime!

370
00:21:32,458 --> 00:21:37,416
[Music]


371
00:21:46,666 --> 00:21:49,541
Your wounds...
Brother...

372
00:21:49,625 --> 00:21:53,916
♪ <i>I am an illusion,</i>

373
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:58,375
♪ <i>A shadow of life once loved.</i>

374
00:21:58,458 --> 00:22:02,458
[Music]

375
00:22:02,541 --> 00:22:04,666
♪ <i>All for you</i>

376
00:22:04,750 --> 00:22:08,250
♪ <i>Fate has dealt you its hand,</i>

377
00:22:08,333 --> 00:22:13,791
♪ <i>Trapped you in a world</i>
<i>you can barely stand.</i>

378
00:22:13,875 --> 00:22:16,666
♪ <i>Will you cower there,</i>

379
00:22:16,750 --> 00:22:21,583
♪ <i>Or rise up and endure?</i>

380
00:22:21,666 --> 00:22:25,916
♪ <i>What to do?</i>

381
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:31,208
♪ <i>Rain has stopped falling,</i>

382
00:22:31,291 --> 00:22:37,083
♪ <i>The sun has stopped shining.</i>

383
00:22:37,166 --> 00:22:40,541
♪ <i>Our luck has left us</i>

384
00:22:40,625 --> 00:22:45,333
♪ <i>On our own.</i>

385
00:22:45,416 --> 00:22:50,375
[Music]

386
00:23:33,333 --> 00:23:37,791
A Shikabane Hime is
forbidden to kill humans.

387
00:23:37,875 --> 00:23:40,750
But what happens when she
faces the one who killed

388
00:23:40,833 --> 00:23:43,541
his own Shikabane Hime?

389
00:23:43,625 --> 00:23:46,166
Beware "Traitor Monk"!

